---
import BaseLayout from '../../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const description = 'A guide to the Vaelinyan Listening Clock, a time artefact that reads season, moons, river movement, and day-part together.';
---
<BaseLayout title="The Listening Clock" description={description}>
  <section class="page-section listening-clock-page">
    <p class="eyebrow">World · Time · Artefact</p>
    <h1>The Listening Clock</h1>
    <p class="lede">The Listening Clock is a Vaelinyan time artefact.</p>
    <p>It reads the season, the two moons, the river’s movement, and the part of the day together. The web version uses a shared UTC reference, so readers in different places see the same Vaelinya reading.</p>

    <article class="clock-artefact" aria-labelledby="clock-title">
      <div class="clock-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Start here</p>
        <h2 id="clock-title">Read the four signs</h2>
        <p>Look from the outside of the clock towards the centre. The Vaelinyan name appears first. The plain meaning appears after it.</p>
        <ol class="clock-start-list">
          <li><strong>Outer ring:</strong> the current Vaelinyan season.</li>
          <li><strong>Moon path:</strong> Aelun and Saelith.</li>
          <li><strong>River path:</strong> how the moons are lifting the water.</li>
          <li><strong>Inner path:</strong> the current Vaelinyan day-part.</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="clock-reading" aria-live="polite">
          <p class="clock-reading-title">Current Vaelinya reading</p>
          <dl class="clock-reading-grid">
            <div><dt>Day part</dt><dd id="clock-day-part">—</dd></div>
            <div><dt>Season</dt><dd id="clock-season">—</dd></div>
            <div><dt>River</dt><dd id="clock-river">—</dd></div>
            <div><dt>Moons</dt><dd>Aelun · Saelith</dd></div>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="clock-shell" aria-label="A live Vaelinyan Listening Clock showing the season, two moons, river, and day.">
        <div class="clock-glow" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <svg class="listening-clock" viewBox="0 0 360 360" role="img" aria-labelledby="clock-svg-title clock-svg-desc">
          <title id="clock-svg-title">The Listening Clock</title>
          <desc id="clock-svg-desc">Four circular paths show the current season, the two moons, the river movement, and the shared Vaelinya day.</desc>

          <circle class="clock-plate" cx="180" cy="180" r="164" />
          <circle class="clock-rim" cx="180" cy="180" r="158" />

          <circle class="path path-season" cx="180" cy="180" r="142" />
          <circle class="path path-moons" cx="180" cy="180" r="111" />
          <circle class="path path-water" cx="180" cy="180" r="82" />
          <circle class="path path-day" cx="180" cy="180" r="54" />

          <circle data-ring="season" class="path-progress season-progress" cx="180" cy="180" r="142" pathLength="1" />
          <circle data-ring="water" class="path-progress water-progress" cx="180" cy="180" r="82" pathLength="1" />
          <circle data-ring="day" class="path-progress day-progress" cx="180" cy="180" r="54" pathLength="1" />

          <circle data-dot="season" class="moving-mark season-mark" r="5" />
          <circle data-dot="aelun" class="moving-mark moon-mark aelun-mark" r="7" />
          <circle data-dot="saelith" class="moving-mark moon-mark saelith-mark" r="4.25" />
          <circle data-dot="water" class="moving-mark water-mark" r="5.5" />
          <circle data-dot="day" class="moving-mark day-mark" r="4.75" />

          <path class="water-thread" id="water-thread" d="M 106 180 Q 132 168 154 180 T 202 180 T 254 180" />

          <circle class="clock-centre" cx="180" cy="180" r="34" />
          <circle class="clock-centre-ring" cx="180" cy="180" r="25" />
          <text class="clock-centre-glyph" x="180" y="187" text-anchor="middle">✧</text>
          <text class="clock-centre-word" id="clock-centre-word" x="180" y="226" text-anchor="middle">Listening</text>
        </svg>

        <div class="clock-key" aria-label="Clock key">
          <span><i class="key-mark season-key"></i>Season</span>
          <span><i class="key-mark moon-key"></i>Moons</span>
          <span><i class="key-mark water-key"></i>River</span>
          <span><i class="key-mark day-key"></i>Day</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="panel read-clock-panel" aria-labelledby="read-clock-title">
      <p class="eyebrow">What the parts mean</p>
      <h2 id="read-clock-title">The clock is read from outside to inside</h2>
      <div class="reading-grid">
        <section><h3>Season</h3><p>The outer ring shows one of the four great seasons. The clock gives the Vaelinyan name first, then the plain meaning.</p></section>
        <section><h3>Moons</h3><p>The two dots are Aelun and Saelith. Their changing positions help shape the river’s movement.</p></section>
        <section><h3>River</h3><p>The river path shows how the water is lifted, calmed, opened, or joined by the moons.</p></section>
        <section><h3>Day</h3><p>The inner path shows the shared Vaelinya day-part, such as Narael for deep rest or Luminel for lampkindle.</p></section>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="panel name-guide-panel" aria-labelledby="name-guide-title">
      <p class="eyebrow">Names used by the clock</p>
      <h2 id="name-guide-title">Vaelinyan names come first</h2>
      <p class="name-guide-intro">The clock’s names describe rest, lifting, opening, joining, and returning. The Vaelinyan name is shown first so the page feels like Vaelinya, and the plain meaning follows so the reader can learn it.</p>

      <div class="name-guide-grid">
        <section class="name-card">
          <p class="name-card-label">Changes during the day</p>
          <h3>Day-part names</h3>
          <ol class="name-list">
            <li><strong>Narael</strong> — deep rest</li>
            <li><strong>Aelwen</strong> — first light</li>
            <li><strong>Risael</strong> — rising day</li>
            <li><strong>Haelora</strong> — high day</li>
            <li><strong>Solaen</strong> — softfall light</li>
            <li><strong>Luminel</strong> — lampkindle</li>
            <li><strong>Aeluna</strong> — moonrise</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="name-card">
          <p class="name-card-label">Changes through the year</p>
          <h3>Season names</h3>
          <ol class="name-list">
            <li><strong>Halarin</strong> — Holding; warmth, memory, and strength are kept safe.</li>
            <li><strong>Lirael</strong> — Loosening; old tightness softens and water begins to move.</li>
            <li><strong>Vaelora</strong> — Opening; paths, flowers, travel, and learning open outward.</li>
            <li><strong>Raelith</strong> — Returning; things come home, rest, change form, and give back.</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="name-card">
          <p class="name-card-label">Changes with the moons</p>
          <h3>River names</h3>
          <ol class="name-list">
            <li><strong>Selmara</strong> — clear-water showing</li>
            <li><strong>Aelma</strong> — moon calm</li>
            <li><strong>Rilava</strong> — first lift</li>
            <li><strong>Rimael</strong> — full river rise</li>
            <li><strong>Duvael</strong> — twin joining</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="name-card">
          <p class="name-card-label">Names that stay steady</p>
          <h3>Moon names</h3>
          <ol class="name-list">
            <li><strong>Aelun</strong> — the larger visible moon</li>
            <li><strong>Saelith</strong> — the smaller older-count moon</li>
          </ol>
        </section>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="visual-callout visual-callout-world story-callout">
      <div class="visual-callout-mark" aria-hidden="true"><span>◌</span></div>
      <div class="visual-callout-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Story note</p>
        <h2>The clock will belong to Lina too</h2>
        <p>One day Lina will find a clock that waits instead of hurrying. This page gives that artefact a clear place in the world first.</p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <div class="link-list">
      <a href="/world/time/">Back to Time</a>
      <a href="/world/time/two-moons/">The Two Moons</a>
      <a href="/world/time/calendar/">Calendar</a>
      <a href="/world/">Back to World</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const TAU = Math.PI * 2;
  const CENTRE = 180;
  const RADIUS = { season: 142, moons: 111, water: 82, day: 54 };
  const SEASONS = [
    { name: 'Halarin', meaning: 'Holding' },
    { name: 'Lirael', meaning: 'Loosening' },
    { name: 'Vaelora', meaning: 'Opening' },
    { name: 'Raelith', meaning: 'Returning' },
  ];

  const rings = new Map(Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('[data-ring]')).map((node) => [node.dataset.ring, node]));
  const dots = new Map(Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('[data-dot]')).map((node) => [node.dataset.dot, node]));
  const centreWord = document.querySelector('#clock-centre-word');
  const waterThread = document.querySelector('#water-thread');
  const dayPartValue = document.querySelector('#clock-day-part');
  const seasonValue = document.querySelector('#clock-season');
  const riverValue = document.querySelector('#clock-river');

  function clamp01(value) { return Math.max(0, Math.min(1, value)); }
  function fractionBetween(value, start, end) { return clamp01((value - start) / (end - start)); }
  function displayName(entry) { return `${entry.name} — ${entry.meaning}`; }

  function cycleFraction(now, cycleDays, offsetDays = 0) {
    const epoch = Date.UTC(2026, 0, 1);
    const elapsedDays = (now.getTime() - epoch) / 86400000;
    return ((elapsedDays + offsetDays) / cycleDays) % 1;
  }

  function setRing(name, progress) {
    const ring = rings.get(name);
    if (ring) ring.style.strokeDashoffset = String(1 - clamp01(progress));
  }

  function setDot(name, progress, radius) {
    const dot = dots.get(name);
    if (!dot) return;
    const value = clamp01(progress);
    const angle = value * TAU - Math.PI / 2;
    dot.setAttribute('cx', String(CENTRE + Math.cos(angle) * radius));
    dot.setAttribute('cy', String(CENTRE + Math.sin(angle) * radius));
  }

  function getDayName(hour) {
    if (hour < 5) return { name: 'Narael', meaning: 'deep rest' };
    if (hour < 8) return { name: 'Aelwen', meaning: 'first light' };
    if (hour < 12) return { name: 'Risael', meaning: 'rising day' };
    if (hour < 15) return { name: 'Haelora', meaning: 'high day' };
    if (hour < 18) return { name: 'Solaen', meaning: 'softfall light' };
    if (hour < 21) return { name: 'Luminel', meaning: 'lampkindle' };
    return { name: 'Aeluna', meaning: 'moonrise' };
  }

  function getRiverName(value) {
    if (value > 0.82) return { name: 'Duvael', meaning: 'twin joining' };
    if (value > 0.62) return { name: 'Rimael', meaning: 'full river rise' };
    if (value > 0.42) return { name: 'Rilava', meaning: 'first lift' };
    if (value > 0.22) return { name: 'Aelma', meaning: 'moon calm' };
    return { name: 'Selmara', meaning: 'clear-water showing' };
  }

  function tick() {
    const now = new Date();
    const utcYear = now.getUTCFullYear();
    const utcHour = now.getUTCHours();
    const utcMinute = now.getUTCMinutes();
    const startOfYear = Date.UTC(utcYear, 0, 1);
    const startOfNextYear = Date.UTC(utcYear + 1, 0, 1);
    const seasonProgress = fractionBetween(now.getTime(), startOfYear, startOfNextYear);
    const day = (utcHour + utcMinute / 60) / 24;
    const aelun = cycleFraction(now, 29.5, 2);
    const saelith = cycleFraction(now, 71, 19);
    const water = (Math.sin(aelun * TAU) + Math.sin(saelith * TAU) + 2) / 4;
    const seasonName = SEASONS[Math.min(3, Math.floor(seasonProgress * 4))];
    const dayName = getDayName(utcHour);
    const riverName = getRiverName(water);

    setRing('season', seasonProgress);
    setRing('water', water);
    setRing('day', day);
    setDot('season', seasonProgress, RADIUS.season);
    setDot('aelun', aelun, RADIUS.moons);
    setDot('saelith', saelith, RADIUS.moons);
    setDot('water', water, RADIUS.water);
    setDot('day', day, RADIUS.day);

    if (waterThread) {
      const lift = Math.round(10 + water * 18);
      waterThread.setAttribute('d', `M 106 180 Q 132 ${180 - lift} 154 180 T 202 180 T 254 180`);
    }

    if (centreWord) centreWord.textContent = seasonName.name;
    if (dayPartValue) dayPartValue.textContent = displayName(dayName);
    if (seasonValue) seasonValue.textContent = displayName(seasonName);
    if (riverValue) riverValue.textContent = displayName(riverName);
  }

  tick();
  window.setInterval(tick, 4000);
</script>

<style>
  .listening-clock-page { box-sizing: border-box; margin-inline: auto; max-width: min(1180px, calc(100vw - 2rem)); width: 100%; }
  .listening-clock-page > .lede, .listening-clock-page > p:not(.eyebrow) { max-width: 58rem; }

  .clock-artefact {
    align-items: center;
    background: radial-gradient(circle at 78% 18%, rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.32), transparent 25%), radial-gradient(circle at 12% 84%, rgba(83, 151, 139, 0.24), transparent 34%), linear-gradient(145deg, rgba(42, 29, 55, 0.98), rgba(87, 67, 91, 0.94) 58%, rgba(49, 70, 69, 0.92));
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.28);
    border-radius: 2.2rem;
    box-shadow: 0 1.4rem 3.4rem rgba(36, 28, 48, 0.22);
    color: #fff8dc;
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(1.25rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.82fr) minmax(300px, 1.18fr);
    margin: 2rem 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    padding: clamp(1.25rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    position: relative;
  }

  .clock-copy, .clock-shell { position: relative; z-index: 1; }
  .clock-copy .eyebrow, .story-callout .eyebrow { color: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.82); }
  .clock-copy h2 { color: #fff8dc; font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.3vw, 3.5rem); letter-spacing: -0.04em; line-height: 0.98; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .clock-copy p, .clock-start-list li { color: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.92); }
  .clock-start-list { display: grid; gap: 0.5rem; margin: 1rem 0 0; padding-left: 1.25rem; }
  .clock-start-list strong { color: #fff8dc; }

  .clock-reading { background: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.14); border: 1px solid rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.22); border-radius: 1.15rem; display: grid; gap: 0.55rem; margin-top: 1.25rem; max-width: 24rem; padding: 0.85rem 1rem; }
  .clock-reading-title { color: #fff8dc !important; font-size: 0.78rem !important; font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: 0.12em; line-height: 1.2; margin: 0 !important; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .clock-reading-grid { display: grid; gap: 0.3rem; margin: 0; }
  .clock-reading-grid div { align-items: baseline; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.14); display: grid; gap: 0.75rem; grid-template-columns: minmax(5.5rem, 0.55fr) minmax(0, 1.45fr); padding-top: 0.35rem; }
  .clock-reading-grid div:first-child { border-top: 0; padding-top: 0; }
  .clock-reading-grid dt, .clock-reading-grid dd { margin: 0; }
  .clock-reading-grid dt { color: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.72); font-size: 0.86rem; font-weight: 800; }
  .clock-reading-grid dd { color: #fff8dc; font-weight: 950; text-align: right; }

  .clock-shell { align-items: center; aspect-ratio: 1; display: grid; justify-items: center; margin-inline: auto; max-width: 560px; width: 100%; }
  .clock-glow { animation: listening-glow 10s ease-in-out infinite; background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.2), rgba(116, 164, 148, 0.14) 38%, transparent 70%); border-radius: 50%; filter: blur(0.28rem); grid-area: 1 / 1; height: 100%; width: 100%; }
  .listening-clock { filter: drop-shadow(0 1rem 2rem rgba(18, 12, 24, 0.32)); grid-area: 1 / 1; height: auto; max-height: 560px; width: min(100%, 560px); }
  .clock-key { align-self: end; background: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.12); border: 1px solid rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.18); border-radius: 999px; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.6rem 0.9rem; grid-area: 1 / 1; justify-content: center; margin-bottom: 0.15rem; padding: 0.55rem 0.8rem; z-index: 2; }
  .clock-key span { align-items: center; color: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.92); display: inline-flex; font-size: 0.86rem; font-weight: 900; gap: 0.35rem; line-height: 1; }
  .key-mark { border-radius: 999px; display: inline-block; height: 0.65rem; width: 0.65rem; }
  .season-key { background: #e7cbff; } .moon-key { background: #fff8dc; } .water-key { background: #77d3d3; } .day-key { background: #ffe899; }

  .clock-plate { fill: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.08); stroke: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.16); stroke-width: 1.5; }
  .clock-rim, .path, .path-progress { fill: none; transform: rotate(-90deg); transform-origin: 180px 180px; }
  .clock-rim { stroke: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.36); stroke-width: 2.5; }
  .path { stroke: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.16); stroke-width: 4.5; }
  .path-moons { stroke-dasharray: 2 10; stroke-linecap: round; }
  .path-water { stroke: rgba(119, 197, 190, 0.24); }
  .path-progress { stroke-dasharray: 1; stroke-dashoffset: 1; stroke-linecap: round; transition: stroke-dashoffset 900ms ease; }
  .season-progress { stroke: rgba(231, 203, 255, 0.72); stroke-width: 5.5; }
  .water-progress { stroke: rgba(119, 211, 211, 0.78); stroke-width: 5; }
  .day-progress { stroke: rgba(255, 232, 153, 0.78); stroke-width: 4.5; }
  .moving-mark { stroke: rgba(42, 29, 55, 0.82); stroke-width: 1.8; }
  .season-mark { fill: #e7cbff; }
  .moon-mark { filter: drop-shadow(0 0 0.55rem rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.72)); stroke-width: 2; }
  .aelun-mark { fill: #fff8dc; } .saelith-mark { fill: #bec8ff; }
  .water-mark { fill: #77d3d3; filter: drop-shadow(0 0 0.55rem rgba(119, 211, 211, 0.66)); }
  .day-mark { fill: #ffe899; }
  .water-thread { fill: none; stroke: rgba(119, 211, 211, 0.48); stroke-linecap: round; stroke-width: 2.5; transition: d 900ms ease; }
  .clock-centre { fill: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.15); stroke: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.34); stroke-width: 2; }
  .clock-centre-ring { fill: rgba(42, 29, 55, 0.58); stroke: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.22); stroke-width: 1.5; }
  .clock-centre-glyph, .clock-centre-word { fill: #fff8dc; font-family: inherit; }
  .clock-centre-glyph { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; }
  .clock-centre-word { font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }

  .read-clock-panel, .name-guide-panel, .story-callout { margin-top: 1rem; }
  .reading-grid, .name-guide-grid { display: grid; gap: 1rem; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr)); margin-top: 1.25rem; }
  .name-guide-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr)); }
  .reading-grid section, .name-card { background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.68); border: 1px solid rgba(68, 44, 88, 0.14); border-radius: 1.1rem; padding: 1rem; }
  .reading-grid h3, .name-card h3 { color: #2b3137; margin-top: 0; }
  .reading-grid p, .name-card p { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .name-guide-intro { max-width: 58rem; }
  .name-card-label { color: rgba(43, 49, 55, 0.68); font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: 0.08em; margin: 0 0 0.4rem !important; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .name-list { display: grid; gap: 0.35rem; margin: 0.8rem 0 0; padding-left: 1.25rem; }
  .name-list li { line-height: 1.35; }

  @keyframes listening-glow { 0%, 100% { opacity: 0.7; transform: scale(0.985); } 50% { opacity: 1; transform: scale(1.025); } }

  @media (max-width: 960px) { .clock-artefact { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .reading-grid, .name-guide-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr)); } }
  @media (max-width: 620px) { .listening-clock-page { max-width: min(100%, calc(100vw - 1rem)); } .clock-artefact { border-radius: 1.35rem; padding: 1rem; } .clock-key { border-radius: 1rem; margin-bottom: -0.2rem; } .clock-reading-grid div { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.15rem; } .clock-reading-grid dd { text-align: left; } .reading-grid, .name-guide-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) { .clock-glow { animation: none; } .path-progress, .water-thread { transition: none; } }
</style>
